    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n               <jats:p>We investigate how communication within banks affects small business lending. Using travel times between a bank\u2019s headquarters and its branches to proxy for the costs of communicating soft information, we exploit shocks to these travel times\u2014the introduction of new airline routes\u2014to evaluate the impact of within-bank communication costs on small business loans. We find that reducing headquarters-branch travel time boosts small business lending in the branch\u2019s county. Several extensions suggest that new airline routes facilitate in-person communications that boost small-firm lending.</jats:p>",
